<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>出版物 |皮尤研究中心</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/publications/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 14:24:31 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>以色列人、巴勒斯坦人、美国人对伊朗战争有不同看法</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/06/09/israelis-palestinians-americans-see-war-in-iran-differently/</link><description>四分之三的以色列人认为美国在攻击伊朗方面做出了正确的决定，而十分之八的巴勒斯坦人则持相反观点。美国人的分歧更大。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 14:24:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/06/09/israelis-palestinians-americans-see-war-in-iran-differently/</guid></item><item><title>大约五分之一的美国人使用过加密货币；共和党人的使用有所增加</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/08/about-1-in-5-americans-have-used-crypto-republicans-use-has-ticked-up/</link><description>加密货币使用中最大的人口差异是性别、年龄和收入。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 01:56:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/08/about-1-in-5-americans-have-used-crypto-republicans-use-has-ticked-up/</guid></item><item><title>万斯是 1.5% 的美国人中皈依天主教的人之一</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/05/vance-is-among-1-5-of-americans-who-have-converted-to-catholicism/</link><description>美国天主教徒中皈依者占 8%。剩下的 92% 的美国天主教徒是在这种信仰中长大的，并且至今仍然认同这种信仰。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 06 Jun 2026 01:59:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/05/vance-is-among-1-5-of-americans-who-have-converted-to-catholicism/</guid></item><item><title>美国人表示，跟上关键新闻话题至关重要。但很少有人说他们自己消息灵通</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/05/americans-say-keeping-up-with-key-news-topics-is-crucial-but-fewer-say-theyre-highly-informed-themselves/</link><description>民主党人和共和党人在评估了解各种话题的重要性方面大体表现出相似的模式。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 06 Jun 2026 01:44:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/05/americans-say-keeping-up-with-key-news-topics-is-crucial-but-fewer-say-theyre-highly-informed-themselves/</guid></item><item><title>36个国家的大多数人对以色列持负面看法，对内塔尼亚胡缺乏信心</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/04/most-people-across-36-countries-have-negative-views-of-israel-and-little-confidence-in-netanyahu/</link><description>在我们调查的大多数国家中，大多数人都对以色列持负面看法，对总理本杰明·内塔尼亚胡 (Benjamin Netanyahu) 缺乏信心或没有信心。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 02:08:02 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/04/most-people-across-36-countries-have-negative-views-of-israel-and-little-confidence-in-netanyahu/</guid></item><item><title>大多数新绿卡发给了已经居住在美国的移民</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/02/majority-of-new-green-cards-have-gone-to-immigrants-already-living-in-us/</link><description>特朗普政府的一份新备忘录可能要求已经在美国的绿卡申请者从国外申请，这可能每年影响数十万人。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 03 Jun 2026 02:37:38 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/02/majority-of-new-green-cards-have-gone-to-immigrants-already-living-in-us/</guid></item><item><title>美国人认为谁会赢得世界杯？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/02/who-do-americans-think-is-going-to-win-the-world-cup/</link><description>大多数美国人表示，他们不太可能关注 2026 年世界杯，尽管移民比美国出生的成年人更有可能收看。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 03 Jun 2026 02:22:38 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/02/who-do-americans-think-is-going-to-win-the-world-cup/</guid></item><item><title>联邦机构 X 账户在特朗普第二个任期内的参与度远高于拜登任期内的参与度</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/01/federal-agency-x-accounts-are-getting-far-more-engagement-in-the-second-trump-term-than-under-biden/</link><description>在特朗普第二届政府中，联邦机构在 X 上的观众参与度比拜登政府最后一年高得多。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 02:33:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/01/federal-agency-x-accounts-are-getting-far-more-engagement-in-the-second-trump-term-than-under-biden/</guid></item><item><title>美国人对避免气候变化最坏影响越来越悲观</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/science/2026/05/28/americans-are-increasingly-pessimistic-about-avoiding-the-worst-effects-of-climate-change/</link><description>大约十分之六的美国人表示，包括美国在内的世界各国在避免气候变化最严重的影响方面做得不够。这种日益增长的悲观情绪是由民主党推动的。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 02:00:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/science/2026/05/28/americans-are-increasingly-pessimistic-about-avoiding-the-worst-effects-of-climate-change/</guid></item><item><title>在全球范围内，四分之一的新车销量是电动汽车或混合动力汽车</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/28/worldwide-a-quarter-of-new-car-sales-are-electric-vehicles-or-hybrids/</link><description>在 8 个国家，2025 年销售的所有新车中至少有一半是电动或混合动力汽车。美国仅达到 10%，远低于 25% 的全球平均水平。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 01:45:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/05/28/worldwide-a-quarter-of-new-car-sales-are-electric-vehicles-or-hybrids/</guid></item></channel></rss>